Colombian Stocks: Canacol Energy, Ecopetrol Fall; ETB Rises

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-08T17:21:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/colombian-stocks-canacol-energy-ecopetrol-fall-etb-rises.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.8 percent to 15,157.24 while the
Colcap Index declined 1 percent to 1,761.71.  Oil producers dropped as crude fell from a 29-month high in
New York while members of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries discussed whether to hold a special meeting.    Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company , dropped 0.8 percent to 3,210 pesos.    Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
fell 1.5 percent to 3,995 pesos.    Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA, the
telecommunications provider serving Colombia’s capital, rose 4.9
percent to 599 pesos, the biggest gain since Dec. 16. The
district of Bogota, ETB’s owner, will decide whether to sell the
company after a shareholder’s meeting scheduled for March 22,
newspaper La Republica reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  